				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\left({T}_{i}, {R}_{i}\right)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M12"><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msub><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> as output. Let <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
