      <sec id="FPar4">
        <title>
          <bold>Proposition 2</bold>
        </title>
        <p id="Par58"><italic>The trimmed average</italic><inline-formula id="IEq63"><alternatives><tex-math id="M137">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{h}{e}_{\left[i\right]}({\widehat{\theta }}^{\left(LTS\right)})=0$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M138"><mml:mrow><mml:mfrac><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:mfrac><mml:msubsup><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>θ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>S</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq63.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>.</p>
        <p id="Par59">That is, the average of the log ratios of the undifferentiated transcript set between a pair of samples is zero after normalization.</p>
        <p>The above describe Part C of the MUREN workflow shown in Fig. <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref>. Next, we explain Part B.</p>
