				\begin{document}$${\Lambda }_{\omega , \psi }$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M144"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">Λ</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ω</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>ψ</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq66.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Assume the criterion in the definition of undifferentiated transcripts sets remain the same across pairs of samples. The undifferentiated transcripts set of all the samples is given by <inline-formula id="IEq67"><alternatives><tex-math id="M145">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
