				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\vartheta =(\mu ,{a}^{\left(1\right)},\dots ,{a}^{\left(I\right)},{b}^{\left(1\right)},\dots ,{b}^{(J)})$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M186"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ϑ</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>μ</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>⋯</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>I</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>⋯</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>J</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq86.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is defined as<disp-formula id="Equd"><alternatives><tex-math id="M187">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{\vartheta }}^{\left(LAD\right)}=\underset{\mu ,{a}^{\left(i\right)},{b}^{(j)}}{\mathrm{argmin}}\sum_{i=1}^{I}\sum_{j=1}^{J}\left|{\widehat{t}}^{(ij)}-\mu -{a}^{(i)}-{b}^{(j)}\right|.$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M188" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>ϑ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mi>A</mml:mi><mml:mi>D</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:munder><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">argmin</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>μ</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:munder><mml:munderover><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>I</mml:mi></mml:munderover><mml:munderover><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>J</mml:mi></mml:munderover><mml:mfenced close="|" open="|"><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mi>μ</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_Equd.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      <p id="Par67">Similar to the results in the three-factor model in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR21">21</xref>], we can show that the LAD estimate is robust in the sense that the influence function of one observation is bounded. The influence function technically measures the effect of infinitesimal perturbation of one data point on the estimates. Not only is the LAD estimate robust, but also has some kind of efficacy. Its <inline-formula id="IEq87"><alternatives><tex-math id="M189">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sqrt{n}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M190"><mml:msqrt><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:msqrt></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq87.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-consistence or asymptotic normality is valid under certain regularity conditions [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR24">24</xref>].</p>
      <p id="Par68">The general LAD can be formulated as a linear programming (LP) problem and thus be solved by the simplex or the interior point algorithm [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR25">25</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR26">26</xref>]. For the specific two-factor model (<xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="">3</xref>), we prefer a simpler method to compute the LAD estimates, namely, the median polish method proposed by Tukey [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR27">27</xref>].</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec9">
      <title>Efficient implementation of computation</title>
      <p id="Par69">In the integration step, one specific model of form (<xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="">3</xref>) is assumed for each transcript, and the model parameters are not assumed to be related across transcripts. Consequently, the integration by median polishing is carried out for each transcript. However, in the single-parameter case where <inline-formula id="IEq88"><alternatives><tex-math id="M191">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\beta =1$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M192"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>β</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq88.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, the integration can be simplified. Suppose in the pairwise normalization step, that the pre-normalized log counts of a specific transcript are <inline-formula id="IEq89"><alternatives><tex-math id="M193">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{t}}^{(ij)}={t}_{i}+{\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M194"><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>α</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq89.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <inline-formula id="IEq90"><alternatives><tex-math id="M195">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M196"><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>α</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq90.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the estimated parameter in the pairwise normalization of the <inline-formula id="IEq91"><alternatives><tex-math id="M197">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M198"><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq91.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-th target with respect to the <inline-formula id="IEq92"><alternatives><tex-math id="M199">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$j$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M200"><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq92.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-th reference. Plug it into model (<xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="">3</xref>), we get<disp-formula id="Eque"><alternatives><tex-math id="M201">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{t}}^{(ij)}={t}_{i}+{\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}=\mu +{a}^{(i)}+{b}^{(j)}+{\epsilon }^{(ij)}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M202" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>α</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>μ</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ϵ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_Eque.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      <p id="Par70">i.e.<disp-formula id="Equf"><alternatives><tex-math id="M203">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}=\mu +\left({a}^{(i)}-{t}_{i}\right)+{b}^{(j)}+{\epsilon }^{(ij)}.$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M204" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>α</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>μ</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ϵ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_Equf.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      <p id="Par71">The models of different transcripts become identical if we reparametrize <inline-formula id="IEq93"><alternatives><tex-math id="M205">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${a}^{(i)}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M206"><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>a</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq93.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> by subtracting corresponding (log) counts <inline-formula id="IEq94"><alternatives><tex-math id="M207">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${t}_{i}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M208"><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq94.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Hence, the transcript-wise integration can be done through the integration of <inline-formula id="IEq95"><alternatives><tex-math id="M209">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M210"><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>α</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4288_Article_IEq95.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>’s. This is proved by the following proposition.</p>
      <sec id="FPar5">
        <title>
          <bold>Proposition 3</bold>
        </title>
        <p id="Par72">(Once-for-all computation) <italic>Consider the following two optimization problems,</italic></p>
        <p id="Par73">
          <italic>M1:</italic>
          <disp-formula id="Equg">
            <alternatives>
              <tex-math id="M211">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{c}\underset{\mu ,{a}^{\left(i\right)},{b}^{\left(j\right)}}{\mathrm{min}}\sum_{i=1}^{I}\sum_{j=1}^{J}\left|{t}_{i}+{\widehat{\alpha }}_{ij}-\mu -{a}^{\left(i\right)}-{b}^{\left(j\right)}\right|\\ \mathrm{s}.\mathrm{t}. \mathrm{median}\left\{{a}^{\left(i\right)}\right\}=\mathrm{median}\left\{{b}^{\left(j\right)}\right\}=0\end{array}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
              <mml:math id="M212" display="block">
                <mml:mrow>
                  <mml:mtable>
                    <mml:mtr>
                      <mml:mtd>
                        <mml:mrow>
                          <mml:munder>
                            <mml:mi mathvariant="normal">min</mml:mi>
                            <mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mi>μ</mml:mi>
                              <mml:mo>,</mml:mo>
                              <mml:msup>
                                <mml:mrow>
                                  <mml:mi>a</mml:mi>
                                </mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                  <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                                </mml:mfenced>
                              </mml:msup>
                              <mml:mo>,</mml:mo>
                              <mml:msup>
                                <mml:mrow>
                                  <mml:mi>b</mml:mi>
                                </mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                  <mml:mi>j</mml:mi>
                                </mml:mfenced>
                              </mml:msup>
                            </mml:mrow>
                          </mml:munder>
                          <mml:msubsup>
                            <mml:mo>∑</mml:mo>
                            <mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                              <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                              <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                            </mml:mrow>
                            <mml:mi>I</mml:mi>
                          </mml:msubsup>
                          <mml:msubsup>
                            <mml:mo>∑</mml:mo>
                            <mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mi>j</mml:mi>
                              <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                              <mml:mn>1</mml:mn>
                            </mml:mrow>
                            <mml:mi>J</mml:mi>
                          </mml:msubsup>
                          <mml:mfenced close="|" open="|">
                            <mml:msub>
                              <mml:mi>t</mml:mi>
                              <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                            </mml:msub>
                            <mml:mo>+</mml:mo>
                            <mml:msub>
                              <mml:mover accent="true">
                                <mml:mi>α</mml:mi>
                                <mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo>
                              </mml:mover>
                              <mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mrow>
                            </mml:msub>
                            <mml:mo>-</mml:mo>
                            <mml:mi>μ</mml:mi>
                            <mml:mo>-</mml:mo>
                            <mml:msup>
                              <mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mi>a</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mfenced>
                            </mml:msup>
                            <mml:mo>-</mml:mo>
                            <mml:msup>
                              <mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mi>b</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                <mml:mi>j</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mfenced>
                            </mml:msup>
                          </mml:mfenced>
                        </mml:mrow>
                      </mml:mtd>
                    </mml:mtr>
                    <mml:mtr>
                      <mml:mtd>
                        <mml:mrow>
                          <mml:mrow/>
                          <mml:mi mathvariant="normal">s</mml:mi>
                          <mml:mo>.</mml:mo>
                          <mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi>
                          <mml:mo>.</mml:mo>
                          <mml:mi mathvariant="normal">median</mml:mi>
                          <mml:mfenced close="}" open="{">
                            <mml:msup>
                              <mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mi>a</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                <mml:mi>i</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mfenced>
                            </mml:msup>
                          </mml:mfenced>
                          <mml:mo>=</mml:mo>
                          <mml:mi mathvariant="normal">median</mml:mi>
                          <mml:mfenced close="}" open="{">
                            <mml:msup>
                              <mml:mrow>
                                <mml:mi>b</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mrow>
                              <mml:mfenced close=")" open="(">
                                <mml:mi>j</mml:mi>
                              </mml:mfenced>
